The paper deals with distributed algorithms, self-stabilization, and fault detection, which are all topics commonly studied in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also focuses on minimum spanning tree (MST) algorithms, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of proof labeling schemes and local verification of proofs suggests a connection to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also discusses time and space complexity, which is relevant to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on fault detection and self-stabilization suggests a connection to the cs.Distributed Computing sub-category.
